1 unit Tomato
¼ ounce Dill
4 tablespoon Sabra Singles
1 teaspoon Garlic Powder
1 unit Green Olives
1 unit Mini Cucumber
5 teaspoon Red Wine Vinegar
2.5 ounce Israeli Couscous
10 ounce Chopped Chicken Breast
Salt
Pepper
Cooking Oil
Olive Oil

• In a small pot, combine couscous, half
the garlic powder, and 3⁄4 cup water
(1 1⁄2 cups for 4 servings). Bring to a boil,
then cover and reduce to a low simmer.
Cook until tender, 10-12 minutes.
• Keep covered off heat until ready to
use in Step 5.

• While couscous cooks, wash and dry
produce.
• Dice tomato into 1⁄4-inch pieces. Trim
and quarter cucumber lengthwise;
cut crosswise into 1⁄4-inch-thick pieces.
Drain and rinse olives, then roughly
chop. Pick and roughly chop fronds
from dill.

• Open package of chicken* and drain
off any excess liquid. Season with salt
and pepper.
• Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Add chicken and
cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked
through, 4-6 minutes.

• While chicken cooks, in a small bowl,
combine SabraTM Classic Hummus,
remaining garlic powder, 1 TBSP olive
oil, and 2 tsp vinegar (2 TBSP olive oil
and 4 tsp vinegar for 4 servings). (Save
remaining vinegar for another use.)
• Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture
reaches a drizzling consistency.

• In a large bowl, combine couscous,
tomato, cucumber, olives, half the
dill, half the chicken, and a drizzle of
olive oil. Taste and season with salt
and pepper.

• Divide dilly couscous between
shallow bowls. Top with remaining
chicken and drizzle with creamy
hummus sauce. Garnish with
remaining dill and serve.

***Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.***